Package: pumacbsacrosswalk
Type: Standalone data product
Title: PUMA-to-CBSA Crosswalk (NLIHC Gap Report 2026 Methodology)
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: person("AEI Housing Center", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "housing@aei.org")
Description: Documents, builds, and shares the PUMA-to-CBSA crosswalk used in
    the AEI Housing Center's replication of the NLIHC Gap Report 2026. Assigns
    every 2022-vintage PUMA to a 2020-vintage Core-Based Statistical Area via
    the Geocorr 2022 50-percent population rule, patches Connecticut from the
    IPUMS MSA2023-PUMA2020 crosswalk, and flags metropolitan vs micropolitan
    status from the OMB 2023 delineation file. Fully offline and deterministic.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Depends: R (>= 4.3)
Imports:
    arrow,
    dplyr,
    here,
    readr,
    readxl,
    stringr
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Encoding: UTF-8
